Leading stadium construction expert and CEO of Monimichelle , Ebi Egbe  has declared his  readiness to help  fix the problematic playing turf of the recently renovated Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja. Egbe said all that the turf needed  is the touch of an expert who understands the pyrotechnics of what a modern stadium turf should look like. He stated that whatever money that is pumped into the turf would go down the drain if it is not handled by thoroughbred professional grounds men. “This is my sector and I know what I am talking about,” he said. “Nigerians were not happy with what they saw of the pitch when we played against  Sierra Leone and I am ready to help as a patriotic Nigerian.   Osimhen tips ‘united’ Eagles for glory       Nigeria ‘ll host best World Fencing Championships , says…     Team Nigeria’s performance thrills AFN boss   “ I have always said my company Monimichelle is ready to partner both states and federal government to eradicate bad pitches in the country; the pitches we have done in the country are there for people to see. “From Aba to Lagos, Katsina , Makurdi, Awka, Yenagoa and Remo what we have done are there and our job speaks for us. “ I don’t compromise quality and as a nation, we should have the best of pitches in Abuja and Lagos,” he added. Meanwhile, Egbe has commended  the Minister for Youth & Sports Development Sunday Dare for  getting  both Alhaji Aliko Dangote and Sir Kesington Adebukunola Adebutu( Baba Ijebu) to  respectively renovate the Abuja and  Lagos stadiums. He , however,  called on   the  minister to ensure  that  quality job is being done at the sporting edifices  in order to impress  the business moguls for their  huge money spent.